WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:35.000
We defined psychological safety as a prerequisite for innovation — but let's visualize why. Imagine asking your clinical team to walk a tightrope: to speak up against a senior attending, or propose a radical new workflow. If there's no safety net, they'll stick to the script. They'll walk rigidly, because a single fall means professional ruin. But if you, as the leader, build a massive safety net — where failure is treated as data, not a punishable offense — your team will suddenly feel empowered to take the creative risks that innovation requires.
